# Part 2 — Describe a live sports event you watched before

One live sports event I remember very clearly was a basketball game I watched last year. It was a CBA match held in Changchun, and as someone who really enjoys basketball and competitive sports, it was an unforgettable experience for me.

The match took place during the winter holiday, around January, in a large indoor stadium near the city center. I went there with two of my close friends from university. We had been planning to watch a live game for quite a long time because we usually only watched basketball on our phones or laptops. So when we finally had the chance to experience it in person, we were all extremely excited.

The atmosphere in the stadium was honestly incredible. The moment the players entered the court, the entire crowd started cheering loudly, waving flags and shouting slogans for their favorite teams. Even though I had watched hundreds of basketball games online before, the live experience was completely different. You could actually hear the players communicating on the court, the sound of sneakers sliding across the floor, and the reactions of thousands of fans around you. It felt much more intense and emotional.

What impressed me most was the final quarter. The two teams were tied for most of the game, and in the last minute one player scored an amazing three-pointer that completely changed the result. The whole stadium exploded with excitement, and everyone around me jumped up and screamed. At that moment, I truly understood why people love watching sports live.

Overall, I felt thrilled and deeply engaged throughout the event. It was not only entertaining, but also a great way to relax and bond with friends. Since then, I’ve become even more interested in attending live sporting events whenever I get the opportunity.

### 中文翻译：

我印象特别深的一场现场体育赛事是去年看的一场篮球比赛。那是一场在长春举行的CBA比赛。作为一个非常喜欢篮球和竞技运动的人，那次经历让我非常难忘。

比赛是在寒假期间，大概一月份举行的，地点在市中心附近的一座大型室内体育馆。我和两个大学里的好朋友一起去看的。我们之前已经计划很久想现场看比赛了，因为平时我们基本都只是在手机或者电脑上看篮球。所以当终于有机会亲自去现场时，我们都特别兴奋。

现场氛围真的非常震撼。当球员入场时，全场观众都在大声欢呼，挥舞旗帜，为自己支持的球队呐喊。虽然我以前在网上看过很多篮球比赛，但现场体验完全不同。你能听到球员在场上的交流声、球鞋摩擦地板的声音，还有周围成千上万球迷的反应，一切都更加真实、激烈、充满情绪。

最让我印象深刻的是最后一节比赛。两支球队大部分时间比分都很接近，而在最后一分钟，一名球员投进了一个非常精彩的三分球，直接改变了比赛结果。整个体育馆瞬间沸腾，周围所有人都站起来尖叫。那一刻我真正理解了为什么人们如此喜欢现场看体育比赛。

总的来说，我整个过程都感到非常激动和投入。这不仅仅是一场娱乐活动，也是一种放松和增进朋友感情的方式。从那以后，我变得更加喜欢现场观看体育赛事了。

